name: Release v1.0.16
body:
* Support returning history in `.fit()` function if `validation_data` is not provided.
* Pin the TF version to 2.5.0 or lower.

name: v1.0.15
body:
* Adapt to KerasTuner 1.0.3.
* Raise the minimum version requirement for KerasTuner to 1.0.3.

name: v1.0.14
body:
* Support TensorFlow 2.5.0.
* Beta release of Timeseries Forecasting. [Tutorial](https://autokeras.com/tutorial/timeseries_forecaster/)
* More blocks support passing hyperparameters to arguments. Including BertBlock, RNNBlock, Transformer, and Embedding. [Code Example](https://github.com/keras-team/autokeras/pull/1408#issue-513508084)
* Support `verbose` argument for `AutoModel.fit`, `AutoModel.predict`, and `AutoModel.evaluate`.
* Move the download of weights of pretrained BERT to GitHub assets.

name: v1.0.13 Release
body:
* Support TensorFlow 2.5.0.
* Beta release of Timeseries Forecasting. [Tutorial](https://autokeras.com/tutorial/timeseries_forecaster/)
* More blocks support passing hyperparameters to arguments. Including BertBlock, RNNBlock, Transformer, and Embedding. [Code Example](https://github.com/keras-team/autokeras/pull/1408#issue-513508084)
* Support `verbose` argument for `AutoModel.fit`, `AutoModel.predict`, and `AutoModel.evaluate`.

name: v1.0.12 Release
body:
* Compatible with TensorFlow 2.4.
* Support specify search space for `num_units`, `num_layers`, and `dropout` of DenseBlock. [Code Example](https://github.com/keras-team/autokeras/pull/1408#issue-513508084)
* Support specify search space for `filters`, `num_blocks`, and `num_layers` of ConvBlock.
* Add Keras Tuner to dependency to be installed automatically.
* Bug fix for multi-model data `AutoModel.predict(...)`.

name: v1.0.11 Release
body:
* Compatible with TensorFlow 2.4.
* Support specify search space for `num_units`, `num_layers`, and `dropout` of DenseBlock. [Code Example](https://github.com/keras-team/autokeras/pull/1408#issue-513508084)

name: v1.0.10 Release
body:
* Reduces `batch_size` by 2 when running out of memory.
* Add pretrained EfficientNet to the search space.
* Support load data from disk. For more details, read our tutorials on the official [website](https://autokeras.com/tutorial/load/).
* Put data type casting and reshaping into the exported Keras Model.
* Fixed the bug of breaking when validation_data is a tf.data.Dataset instance.

name: v1.0.9 Release
body:
* Improved text data performance by adding pretrained BERT model to the search space.
* Added Adam optimizer with weight decay to the search space.

name: v1.0.8 Release
body:
* Performance improvements for structured data classification and regression tasks.
* Bug fix for not using the best number of epochs for the final model training when validation data is not provided.

name: v1.0.7 Release
body:
* Bug fix for using multiple GPUs.
* Bug fix for KeyError when searching for large number of trials.
* Grammar fixes for error messages.

name: v1.0.6 Release
body:
* Reduced GPU memory consumption.
* Optimized greedy tuning algorithm.
* Support using multiple GPUs.

name: v1.0.5 Release
body:
* Updated TF dependency version to 2.3.0.
* Bug fix for checkpoint not found during evaluate and predict.

name: v1.0.4 Release
body:
Bug Fixes:
* Fixed fit the final model only one epoch after search all the trials.
* Fixed the checkpoint not found issue during fit.

New Features:
* Add pretrained XceptionNet and ResNet with ImageNet weights to the search space of image tasks.
* Enlarge the search space for more optimizers and laerning rates.
* Transformer model included in the search space.

API Changes:
* ResNetBlock and XceptionBlock `pooling` argument removed.
* All task APIs use `overwrite=False` by default.
* Change all `dropout_rate` arguments to `dropout`.

name: v1.0.3 Release
body:
Bump dependency TensorFlow version to 2.2.0.
User now can use custom metrics and loss.
User now can specify the tuner to use for Task APIs like ImageClassifier.
Use Keras preprocessing layers for ImageAugmentation.
If not epochs is not specified, and validation_data is not provided,
it will use the best models best number of epochs for retraining the best model with the entire training set.
Bug fixes:
All bugs in the tutorials are fixed.
All the tutorials can run smoothly.
Breaking changes:
ImageAugmentation args updated.

name: v1.0.2 Release
body:
Fixed the bug for low performance in the final model training.
Fixed the bug for does not support tf.data.Dataset for TextClassifier.
Improved performance for ImageClassifier and TextClassifier.

Issues:
It cannot save the preprocessing layers' weights.
The exported model has to be adapted manually if contains any preprocessing layer.
It should be fixed with TF 2.2.
We will have another release afterward.

name: v1.0.1 Release
body:
Supporting Tensorflow Keras preprocessing layers.
The preprocessors are now exportable to Keras Model, too,
i.e., the entire model is exportable to Keras Model.
The exported model should have exactly the sample performances as the searched model.

Redesigned the API and system architecture based on KerasTuner 1.0 and TensorFlow 2.0.
Refer to the official website for more information. https://autokeras.com/

Use BERT to do the natural language tasks.
Pretrained models separated out to autokeras-pretrained.
Tabular module separated out to autokaggle.

Fixed some bugs.
Code refactored.

Added Predefined API.
Added pretrained models of face detection, object detection, voice generation.

Fixed the CUDA: out of memory bug.
Refined the interface for net_module.
Improved neural architecture search performance.
Fixed the bug in dependencies of setup.py
A comparatively stable version.
Fixed the memory limit bug.
Refined the output information on screen.
Updated output information.
Fixing the bugs caused by floating point.
Fixed some bugs.
Adaptive memory to avoid out of memory error.
Fixed the bug in evaluation always output 100.0.

Fixed the bug in the evaluation.
limited the memory usage with Constant.MAX_MODEL_SIZE.
Changed dependency to tensorflow 1.10.0.
Fixed the bug in setup.py
Update setup.py (#147 )

Reformat the standard output.
Further limited the search space.
Fixed a bug of deeper dense layer.

Use torch.multiprocessing to avoid the error caused by multiprocessing in Windows.

Limit the model size to avoid memory overflow.
Solve the timeout error.
ImageRegressor is added to Auto Keras.

0.2.0
Backend switched from Keras to Pytorch.

Docs to be added.
performance to be fine-tuned.
